  Part 2: RATIOS AND GROWTH RATE
======================================================================

Growth ratios T(n+1)/T(n):
  T( 2)/T( 1) =     1.000000
  T( 3)/T( 2) =     3.000000
  T( 4)/T( 3) =     3.333333
  T( 5)/T( 4) =     3.800000
  T( 6)/T( 5) =     4.052632
  T( 7)/T( 6) =     4.246753
  T( 8)/T( 7) =     4.389908
  T( 9)/T( 8) =     4.501916
  T(10)/T( 9) =     4.591489
  T(11)/T(10) =     4.664841
  T(12)/T(11) =     4.725992
  T(13)/T(12) =     4.777755
  T(14)/T(13) =     4.822136
  T(15)/T(14) =     4.860609
  T(16)/T(15) =     4.894279
  T(17)/T(16) =     4.923994
  T(18)/T(17) =     4.950411

The growth constant rho = lim T(n+1)/T(n):
  Estimated: 4.99532864

Generating function: y = x + y^2 + y^3
Singular point equation: 1 = 2y + 3y^2
Solution: 3y^2 + 2y - 1 = 0 => (3y-1)(y+1) = 0
  y_c = 1/3 = 1/KEY2 !!!

  x_c = y_c - y_c^2 - y_c^3 = 1/3 - 1/9 - 1/27 = 5/27
  x_c = 5/27 = 0.1851851852
  Growth constant rho = 1/x_c = 5.4000000000

  rho = 5.4000000000
  rho = 27/5 = 5.4 exactly? True
  27/5 = KEY2^3 / KEY_SUM = KEY2^3 / (KEY1+KEY2)

  *** The growth constant of the (2,3)-operad is KEY2^3/(KEY1+KEY2) = 27/5 ***

