======================================================================
  Part 6: GENERATING FUNCTION — ALGEBRAIC EQUATION
======================================================================

The generating function y(x) = sum T(n) x^n satisfies:

  y = x + y^2 + y^3

This is a CUBIC in y: y^3 + y^2 - y + x = 0

Discriminant of the cubic (in y):
  p = 1, q = -1, r = x  (y^3 + y^2 - y + x = 0)

Depressed cubic (substitute y = t - 1/3):
  t^3 - (4/3)t + (8/27 + x) = 0

Coefficients: p = -4/3, q = 8/27 + x
  p = -4/3 = -KEY1^2 / KEY2
  When x = 0: q = 8/27 = KEY1^3 / KEY2^3

Singular points (discriminant = 0):
  x = 8/27 = 0.2962962963 = KEY1^3/KEY2^3
  x = -8/9 = -0.8888888889 = -KEY1^3/KEY2^2

  The physical singular point is x_c = 8/27 = (KEY1/KEY2)^3
  The growth constant is 1/x_c = 27/8 = (KEY2/KEY1)^3

  CORRECTION: x_c = y_c - y_c^2 - y_c^3 = 1/3 - 1/9 - 1/27 = 5/27
  rho = 1/x_c = 27/5 = 27/5 = 5.4
  27/5 = KEY2^KEY2 / KEY_SUM

  But note: 5/27 = KEY_SUM / KEY2^KEY2
  And 27 = KEY2^KEY2, 5 = KEY_SUM

  Verification: T(20)/T(19) = 4.99532864
  27/5 = 5.40000000
  Match: False

